# List All Payments

Retrieves a list of `PaymentIntent` objects. The results are returned in reverse chronological order, with the most recent transactions appearing first. Use this endpoint to audit transactions or populate order history in your application.

**Base URL** : https://api.paymentservice.com/v1

**Endpoint** : payments

**Method** : GET

**Sample URL** : https://sandbox-api.paymentservice.com/v1/payments?limit=2&status=succeeded`

## Authentication
Authenticate your request by including your secret key in the `Authorization` header.
`Authorization: Bearer <YOUR_SECRET_KEY>`

### Query Parameters
Query parameters allow you to filter and paginate the results returned by the API.

| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **`limit`** | Integer | `10` | The number of objects to return. Min: `1`, Max: `100`. |
| **`starting_after`** | String | `null` | A cursor for use in pagination. Provide an object `id` to fetch the next page of results. |
| **`status`** | String | `null` | Filter by state: `requires_payment_method`, `processing`, `succeeded`, `canceled`. |
| **`customer`** | String | `null` | Only return payments for a specific customer ID (e.g., `cus_987...`). |
| **`created[gte]`** | Timestamp | `null` | Return payments created on or after this Unix timestamp. |

### Sample Request
```
curl -G [https://sandbox-api.paymentservice.com/v1/payments](https://sandbox-api.paymentservice.com/v1/payments) \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer sk_test_4eC39H..." \
  -d limit=2 \
  -d status=succeeded`
  ```

